1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:40,000
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

2
00:00:49,404 --> 00:00:52,073
STILL SHINING

3
00:00:55,076 --> 00:01:00,081
DECEMBER 2015

4
00:01:00,165 --> 00:01:01,583
Your internship's over,

5
00:01:01,666 --> 00:01:03,501
but can you even make it home
in this weather?

6
00:01:04,169 --> 00:01:05,378
Nothing will be running.

7
00:01:06,129 --> 00:01:07,463
But I have to go.

8
00:01:07,547 --> 00:01:09,549
I heard you got
the only internship for Hawaii.

9
00:01:09,632 --> 00:01:11,301
I bet you'll be there before Christmas.

10
00:01:11,384 --> 00:01:12,385
Lucky you.

11
00:01:13,261 --> 00:01:14,262
I'm not going to go.

12
00:01:15,013 --> 00:01:16,931
I don't think I'm cut out
for this line of work.

13
00:01:17,807 --> 00:01:19,142
I'm going back to school.

14
00:01:27,192 --> 00:01:28,026
That's…

15
00:01:29,944 --> 00:01:32,488
It's a miniature Sea Train.
They're local souvenirs.

16
00:01:42,040 --> 00:01:43,041
Can I ask something?

17
00:01:44,500 --> 00:01:46,294
Breaking up over the phone

18
00:01:47,128 --> 00:01:48,630
doesn't count as a breakup, right?

19
00:01:49,547 --> 00:01:50,840
Breaking up over the phone?

20
00:01:52,383 --> 00:01:54,010
That's a bit…

21
00:01:56,387 --> 00:01:57,430
So…

22
00:01:58,389 --> 00:01:59,641
we're not broken up.

23
00:02:00,934 --> 00:02:02,894
It's okay for me to see him.

24
00:02:05,104 --> 00:02:08,233
I have to make it back today.
Can I pay for this with a card?

25
00:02:09,067 --> 00:02:10,276
Give me five minutes.

26
00:02:12,195 --> 00:02:14,572
Please text me.
I'll transfer the money to you.

27
00:02:14,656 --> 00:02:15,490
I have to go.

28
00:02:17,158 --> 00:02:19,327
-Thanks.
-Get home safe.

29
00:02:22,288 --> 00:02:25,291
Tae-seo, I miss you so much.

30
00:02:26,626 --> 00:02:30,255
The thought of seeing you makes me wonder
how I even managed without you.

31
00:02:31,422 --> 00:02:34,175
I have so much to tell you
and so much to explain.

32
00:02:36,261 --> 00:02:37,512
I have to go see you right now.

33
00:02:54,529 --> 00:02:55,363
Rescue,

34
00:02:55,446 --> 00:02:57,615
are you able to respond
to Yeonwoo right now?

35
00:02:57,699 --> 00:02:59,242
I'm going to Yeonwoo too.

36
00:02:59,325 --> 00:03:01,911
Can you take me there with you?

37
00:03:04,080 --> 00:03:06,916
Able to respond.

38
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:08,960
The caller from Yeonwoo is stranded.

39
00:03:09,043 --> 00:03:11,337
We've sent the caller's number.
Contact them directly.

40
00:03:12,505 --> 00:03:13,631
Copy that.

41
00:03:18,803 --> 00:03:20,346
Hello? This is the rescue unit.

42
00:03:21,973 --> 00:03:23,266
Please go ahead.

43
00:03:23,349 --> 00:03:25,977
We're on the road
leading to the Yeonwoo village hall.

44
00:03:26,060 --> 00:03:28,229
We live here in Yeonwoo.

45
00:03:28,312 --> 00:03:30,523
I know where that is.
I'm also from Yeonwoo.

46
00:03:30,606 --> 00:03:31,774
I'll help.

47
00:03:32,734 --> 00:03:35,570
Ma'am, I'm with someone
who knows the area.

48
00:03:35,653 --> 00:03:38,406
Just leave your car
and go back inside your house.

49
00:03:39,115 --> 00:03:41,784
The roads are pretty bad,
so it'll take me a while.

50
00:03:42,577 --> 00:03:45,455
Gosh, my grandson
left for the army this morning,

51
00:03:45,538 --> 00:03:47,165
but he went alone.

52
00:03:47,248 --> 00:03:50,084
All because our truck
got stuck in the snow.

53
00:03:50,168 --> 00:03:51,794
Please come get our truck out.

54
00:03:51,878 --> 00:03:55,757
Even if we were late, we wanted to go
after getting our truck out,

55
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:58,509
but it got stuck in the snow again.

56
00:03:59,093 --> 00:04:02,221
We should've at least been there
to see Tae-seo get his hair cut.

57
00:04:03,765 --> 00:04:08,561
Goodness, that poor boy
went to that scary place all by himself.

58
00:04:09,479 --> 00:04:12,774
He's endured so much by himself.

59
00:04:12,857 --> 00:04:17,278
My goodness, we should at least be there
to see him enter the training center.

60
00:04:17,362 --> 00:04:18,946
But Tae-seo went alone.

61
00:04:19,030 --> 00:04:22,408
He shouldn't have gone alone.

62
00:04:36,631 --> 00:04:40,009
FIRE RESCUE

63
00:04:40,093 --> 00:04:43,012
COMMUNITY SAFETY UNIT

64
00:04:44,639 --> 00:04:46,224
Gosh, thank you so much.

65
00:04:46,307 --> 00:04:47,934
The wheels are just spinning.

66
00:04:48,017 --> 00:04:49,977
-It's cold, so please wait in our car.
-Right.

67
00:04:51,354 --> 00:04:52,188
Come on out.

68
00:04:52,271 --> 00:04:53,231
All right.

69
00:04:53,314 --> 00:04:54,607
Okay, be careful.

70
00:04:55,274 --> 00:04:56,109
There you go.

71
00:04:56,192 --> 00:04:57,652
Watch out. Slowly.

72
00:06:31,662 --> 00:06:35,791
Will I be able to explain to him?

73
00:06:39,045 --> 00:06:45,885
STILL SHINING

74
00:06:55,228 --> 00:06:56,479
Rule Tongyeong out as well.

75
00:07:02,944 --> 00:07:03,861
Don't go there.

76
00:07:06,405 --> 00:07:07,240
Tae-seo.

77
00:07:08,407 --> 00:07:10,159
Right now…

78
00:07:12,954 --> 00:07:15,790
isn't a good time to talk.

79
00:07:16,832 --> 00:07:18,960
I'll call you back soon.

80
00:07:47,071 --> 00:07:48,739
YEON NAMSAN

81
00:07:52,201 --> 00:07:53,494
If you're home, let's meet.

82
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:00,668
I'm not in Seoul.

83
00:08:01,794 --> 00:08:04,005
I'll call you back tomorrow.

84
00:08:31,490 --> 00:08:34,076
Hi, Grandpa. I'm about to leave now.

85
00:08:34,744 --> 00:08:36,329
Yes, you need to use the truck.

86
00:08:36,412 --> 00:08:39,123
You must be tired
after running the trains all day.

87
00:08:39,206 --> 00:08:41,042
There's no need to hurry.

88
00:08:43,628 --> 00:08:45,338
I'm going to leave now.

89
00:08:45,421 --> 00:08:46,505
Okay, bye.

90
00:08:52,386 --> 00:08:54,221
I'M NOT IN SEOUL
I'LL CALL YOU BACK TOMORROW

91
00:09:32,843 --> 00:09:34,637
What time do you finish work today?

92
00:09:48,401 --> 00:09:49,652
Did you finish your shift?

93
00:09:51,195 --> 00:09:52,655
I'm at the hospital.

94
00:09:52,738 --> 00:09:53,823
In Gangneung.

95
00:09:55,074 --> 00:09:56,117
Where are you?

96
00:09:57,326 --> 00:09:58,160
Seoul.

97
00:10:01,330 --> 00:10:02,164
And yesterday?

98
00:10:04,750 --> 00:10:06,127
I asked you to rule out Tongyeong,

99
00:10:07,169 --> 00:10:08,754
but you haven't given me an answer yet.

100
00:10:10,256 --> 00:10:12,133
I'll explain everything in person.

101
00:10:13,926 --> 00:10:16,554
So there's something
you've needed to explain since yesterday?

102
00:10:19,598 --> 00:10:20,766
What is it?

103
00:10:30,359 --> 00:10:31,819
All right. Let's meet up.

104
00:10:32,403 --> 00:10:34,947
I can be in Seoul before midnight.
Where should I go to see you?

105
00:10:35,865 --> 00:10:37,116
Well…

106
00:10:38,534 --> 00:10:39,577
I…

107
00:10:40,745 --> 00:10:42,997
only have time right now.

108
00:10:44,206 --> 00:10:46,292
You were going to see me briefly

109
00:10:46,375 --> 00:10:50,379
to explain what had changed so suddenly
in that short amount of time

110
00:10:50,463 --> 00:10:51,756
and then go back?

111
00:10:51,839 --> 00:10:54,717
We were talking about our future
just the other day.

112
00:11:04,059 --> 00:11:05,394
So when can I see you?

113
00:11:07,521 --> 00:11:09,023
In three days.

114
00:11:14,028 --> 00:11:15,029
Fine.

115
00:11:35,007 --> 00:11:36,592
Tae-seo.

116
00:11:38,385 --> 00:11:41,472
-It's not visiting hours yet, is it?
-No.

117
00:11:43,891 --> 00:11:45,518
My goodness.

118
00:11:46,435 --> 00:11:47,436
Gosh.

119
00:11:50,648 --> 00:11:53,234
Hey, is the truck comfortable?

120
00:11:53,317 --> 00:11:57,196
If you take the bus,
you can at least get some shut-eye.

121
00:11:57,279 --> 00:11:59,114
It's fine. You need to use it.

122
00:11:59,657 --> 00:12:01,200
Come sit.

123
00:12:01,283 --> 00:12:04,203
You must be tired after driving all day.

124
00:12:04,286 --> 00:12:06,580
Grandpa, I'll just be a minute.

125
00:12:44,451 --> 00:12:46,245
-Hello?
-Close the window for me.

126
00:12:47,121 --> 00:12:48,455
I already…

127
00:12:53,836 --> 00:12:54,878
We just missed each other.

128
00:12:55,546 --> 00:12:57,506
Missing each other,
being drained emotionally,

129
00:12:57,590 --> 00:12:59,633
yet still trying our best
to make time to meet…

130
00:13:01,677 --> 00:13:03,345
That's what you struggled with.

131
00:13:04,513 --> 00:13:05,598
You want to do this again?

132
00:13:07,224 --> 00:13:09,435
Even if you're mad at me,
I want to hear it in person.

133
00:13:10,227 --> 00:13:12,521
I'm going to keep coming here
until I see you.

134
00:13:12,605 --> 00:13:14,940
I don't care how many times
we miss each other.

135
00:13:17,401 --> 00:13:19,653
Did anything happen
that I should be worried about?

136
00:13:21,655 --> 00:13:24,742
No, it's nothing like that.

137
00:13:25,618 --> 00:13:26,619
I just…

138
00:13:36,545 --> 00:13:39,089
I really want to talk to you in person.

139
00:13:41,175 --> 00:13:42,134
Please.

140
00:13:43,802 --> 00:13:45,971
I'll tidy up a bit before I go
since I'm already here.

141
00:13:46,055 --> 00:13:47,806
The floor's quite messy.

142
00:13:47,890 --> 00:13:50,476
You must be tired from the trip.
You shouldn't be cleaning up.

143
00:13:53,312 --> 00:13:54,229
Eun-a.

144
00:13:56,357 --> 00:13:58,192
I don't want you to have a hard time.

145
00:14:00,194 --> 00:14:01,487
But…

146
00:14:06,492 --> 00:14:08,619
I don't want that for me either.

147
00:14:09,828 --> 00:14:11,205
At least…

148
00:14:11,955 --> 00:14:13,374
At least for us,

149
00:14:14,500 --> 00:14:16,960
let's not make things hard for each other.

150
00:15:12,641 --> 00:15:13,934
It's not working.

151
00:15:14,601 --> 00:15:16,353
The portable gas stove…

152
00:15:16,437 --> 00:15:17,521
Is it here?

153
00:15:30,492 --> 00:15:33,620
Seong-chan, replacing just one breaker
in the guesthouse won't do it.

154
00:15:34,204 --> 00:15:35,247
They all need replacing.

155
00:15:35,330 --> 00:15:38,250
Eun-a asked me to change just one,
but that won't fix anything.

156
00:15:38,333 --> 00:15:39,710
Please replace all of them.

157
00:15:40,377 --> 00:15:44,548
Mr. Bae, we have a complaint that the room
is different from the booking.

158
00:15:44,631 --> 00:15:46,216
I see. Okay.

159
00:15:56,143 --> 00:15:58,645
-Mom, I'm going to head in first.
-Okay.

160
00:15:59,438 --> 00:16:02,274
-Hi, Ga-on.
-Hello.

161
00:16:08,489 --> 00:16:09,740
Hi, you made it.

162
00:16:10,908 --> 00:16:12,034
Let me get that for you.

163
00:16:15,412 --> 00:16:16,580
You've had it rough.

164
00:16:17,998 --> 00:16:19,500
You're back now. That's what matters.

165
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:21,251
Thank you.

166
00:16:35,265 --> 00:16:36,975
Let me know when the guesthouse is empty.

167
00:16:37,059 --> 00:16:39,019
I'll replace everything real quick.

168
00:16:39,103 --> 00:16:40,813
Seong-chan asked me to do it.

169
00:16:49,363 --> 00:16:51,615
MO EUN-A

170
00:16:57,204 --> 00:16:58,705
If she's back, that's good enough.

171
00:18:29,546 --> 00:18:32,382
Eun-a, I'm in front
of your guesthouse in Tongyeong.

172
00:18:32,466 --> 00:18:35,093
I'm not here as a surprise.
I meant to message you on my way here.

173
00:18:35,177 --> 00:18:36,803
But I ended up driving without stopping.

174
00:18:43,518 --> 00:18:45,145
Yeon Tae-seo.

175
00:18:55,572 --> 00:18:56,823
Is this the place?

176
00:18:56,907 --> 00:18:58,617
No, that one.

177
00:19:06,625 --> 00:19:09,044
-You said we should meet.
-Not here.

178
00:19:16,385 --> 00:19:17,511
Here.

179
00:19:18,303 --> 00:19:20,430
I come here first thing in the morning.

180
00:19:21,848 --> 00:19:23,517
I take a deep breath

181
00:19:24,268 --> 00:19:26,687
and think as much as I want
about the people I miss.

182
00:19:27,604 --> 00:19:30,857
I came here this morning as well
and thought about you a lot.

183
00:19:38,907 --> 00:19:39,992
All right.

184
00:19:40,826 --> 00:19:41,994
I'll explain.

185
00:19:42,536 --> 00:19:44,621
When I heard this place would close down,

186
00:19:44,705 --> 00:19:46,456
my mind went blank.

187
00:19:47,666 --> 00:19:50,127
I heard it would be cleared out
if I didn't come back,

188
00:19:50,210 --> 00:19:51,503
so I came.

189
00:19:51,586 --> 00:19:54,089
-Cleared out?
-They were going to tear it down.

190
00:19:54,172 --> 00:19:56,717
A truck had been camped out
here in front every day.

191
00:19:57,342 --> 00:19:58,385
Even now?

192
00:19:58,468 --> 00:20:00,262
No, that's been resolved.

193
00:20:00,345 --> 00:20:02,431
But when I heard it would close down,

194
00:20:03,181 --> 00:20:05,309
that truck came to mind right away.

195
00:20:05,392 --> 00:20:08,520
I kept picturing that truck
knocking my guesthouse down.

196
00:20:09,980 --> 00:20:11,064
You know me.

197
00:20:11,148 --> 00:20:14,901
When I picture something bad,
I can't get it out of my head.

198
00:20:16,903 --> 00:20:18,655
I wanted to finish things properly myself.

199
00:20:19,448 --> 00:20:20,699
That's why I came.

200
00:20:21,908 --> 00:20:23,452
There was no other reason.

201
00:20:26,288 --> 00:20:27,581
What about your job in Seoul?

202
00:20:28,540 --> 00:20:29,750
You found a room too.

203
00:20:30,625 --> 00:20:32,919
The previous manager
will be working there again.

204
00:20:33,003 --> 00:20:35,922
The room was hers, so she'd agreed
to pass it onto me when she moved out.

205
00:20:36,923 --> 00:20:39,426
But the job she had lined up
was left up in the air,

206
00:20:39,509 --> 00:20:41,303
and I was left hanging too.

207
00:20:46,016 --> 00:20:47,225
Is that everything?

208
00:20:48,352 --> 00:20:50,062
That's the reason I came.

209
00:20:50,145 --> 00:20:52,981
What matters is
what will happen going forward.

210
00:20:54,316 --> 00:20:56,276
I'll only come down here when I need to.

211
00:20:56,360 --> 00:20:58,195
I'll go to Seoul
when I don't have bookings.

212
00:20:58,278 --> 00:21:00,113
The lease is until next March.

213
00:21:00,197 --> 00:21:01,990
As for what happens after,

214
00:21:02,074 --> 00:21:04,201
I'm going to figure it out with you.

215
00:21:05,118 --> 00:21:08,413
I'll be the only one going back and forth,
so you don't have to worry.

216
00:21:09,081 --> 00:21:11,208
We're a couple.
Why let only you do all the work?

217
00:21:12,542 --> 00:21:14,503
I'm the one who pushed for this,

218
00:21:14,586 --> 00:21:16,213
so I should take responsibility.

219
00:21:18,131 --> 00:21:19,549
I'll explain more.

220
00:21:19,633 --> 00:21:21,718
About how I'll go
back and forth on my own…

221
00:21:22,761 --> 00:21:24,012
You've explained enough.

222
00:21:25,055 --> 00:21:26,473
This is where you lived and worked,

223
00:21:27,432 --> 00:21:28,683
and you want to wrap things up.

224
00:21:32,229 --> 00:21:33,271
I get it.

225
00:21:37,359 --> 00:21:39,486
I'll fit however I can into your schedule.

226
00:21:40,695 --> 00:21:42,197
I'm going to make all the effort.

227
00:21:43,073 --> 00:21:44,699
It'll be different from when we were 20.

228
00:21:55,043 --> 00:21:55,919
Okay.

229
00:21:58,547 --> 00:21:59,381
Let's give it a go.

230
00:22:09,057 --> 00:22:10,892
When I'm running a train,

231
00:22:12,227 --> 00:22:14,938
I sometimes have an open view like this.

232
00:22:16,189 --> 00:22:18,525
It's from an angle you can't see
anywhere else in Seoul.

233
00:22:22,320 --> 00:22:24,281
But it's like that
in every direction here.

234
00:22:25,490 --> 00:22:26,867
It's refreshing to look at.

235
00:22:39,171 --> 00:22:41,047
I'm not going to rule out Yeonwoo.

236
00:22:45,093 --> 00:22:47,554
I could maybe get a job
at the hotel there.

237
00:22:48,680 --> 00:22:51,057
I wonder what will it feel like
to commute from home.

238
00:22:51,933 --> 00:22:55,604
Except for when I was on my internship,
I've only lived in the residence hall.

239
00:23:09,701 --> 00:23:10,660
Stay here for a second.

240
00:23:11,620 --> 00:23:12,871
What?

241
00:23:57,374 --> 00:24:00,794
Put these in your grandma's room
so she can see them when she wakes up.

242
00:24:02,003 --> 00:24:03,755
She likes flowers.

243
00:24:04,422 --> 00:24:06,132
She's still a young girl at heart.

244
00:24:10,428 --> 00:24:12,305
They're not allowed in the ICU.

245
00:24:18,853 --> 00:24:21,064
You've never gotten flowers
from a woman before, right?

246
00:24:22,565 --> 00:24:23,400
No.

247
00:24:24,567 --> 00:24:26,194
So I'm your first.

248
00:24:30,615 --> 00:24:32,909
Thank you for coming
all this way to see me.

249
00:24:56,683 --> 00:24:57,600
Hello?

250
00:24:57,684 --> 00:24:59,978
You haven't sent your list
of credit card transactions

251
00:25:00,061 --> 00:25:02,605
and the receipts for your expenses.

252
00:25:03,690 --> 00:25:08,278
I requested them via email.
Please send them in an Excel file.

253
00:25:08,361 --> 00:25:10,488
Your father never asked for any receipts.

254
00:25:11,197 --> 00:25:13,575
All you need is my credit card statement.

255
00:25:13,658 --> 00:25:15,243
He did request them.

256
00:25:16,036 --> 00:25:18,079
What do you mean he never did?
I already checked.

257
00:25:19,122 --> 00:25:21,374
Please send them by the end of this week.

258
00:25:21,458 --> 00:25:22,334
Okay.

259
00:25:22,417 --> 00:25:23,501
Okay, bye.

260
00:25:37,766 --> 00:25:38,808
YEON HUI-SEO

261
00:25:38,892 --> 00:25:40,602
I'm being discharged today.

262
00:25:40,685 --> 00:25:41,936
Thank you for the other day.

263
00:25:42,020 --> 00:25:44,689
If you're ever in this area,
please let me know.

264
00:25:44,773 --> 00:25:46,733
I'll give you the red carpet treatment.

265
00:25:47,567 --> 00:25:48,693
How cute.

266
00:25:53,156 --> 00:25:54,908
I don't even have the strength to type.

267
00:26:00,747 --> 00:26:03,124
I've been sitting down all day.

268
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:06,044
My muscles are wasting away.

269
00:26:13,009 --> 00:26:14,928
I wonder when he'll come by to do it.

270
00:26:20,308 --> 00:26:22,477
-Tae-seo.
-Hello.

271
00:26:23,353 --> 00:26:25,188
Why do you seem so tired?

272
00:26:25,271 --> 00:26:28,733
The tunnel section
felt unusually long today.

273
00:26:30,193 --> 00:26:31,986
Gosh, I was concentrating too hard.

274
00:26:33,363 --> 00:26:35,824
There's nothing like this
when you're tired.

275
00:26:40,120 --> 00:26:41,913
Thank you. I needed this.

276
00:26:51,047 --> 00:26:52,340
It's great.

277
00:26:52,424 --> 00:26:53,425
Can I take this?

278
00:26:53,508 --> 00:26:54,426
Sure.

279
00:26:54,509 --> 00:26:55,593
Thank you.

280
00:27:31,629 --> 00:27:32,672
Are you working right now?

281
00:27:33,465 --> 00:27:34,340
Or running?

282
00:27:35,884 --> 00:27:38,011
Or riding a public rental bike home?

283
00:27:39,179 --> 00:27:40,889
I don't have any bookings
after this guest.

284
00:27:41,556 --> 00:27:42,640
I'll come to Seoul.

285
00:27:44,184 --> 00:27:46,853
I'm definitely going to follow
your routine this time.

286
00:27:48,396 --> 00:27:52,901
I always wondered what you look at
on your way home every day.

287
00:28:05,163 --> 00:28:07,540
Ga-on said he was the dinosaur king.

288
00:28:07,624 --> 00:28:10,293
-Right, he did!
-He went all the way down there.

289
00:28:10,376 --> 00:28:12,128
-What are you talking about?
-To calm him…

290
00:28:13,880 --> 00:28:15,507
When he was playing with Da-gyeong…

291
00:28:35,527 --> 00:28:37,946
If I went a little past Gwanghwamun,

292
00:28:39,697 --> 00:28:42,116
I used to be able
to at least briefly see her.

293
00:29:04,138 --> 00:29:05,223
Grandpa?

294
00:29:05,306 --> 00:29:06,599
Yes, go ahead.

295
00:29:06,683 --> 00:29:07,725
Right, so…

296
00:29:07,809 --> 00:29:10,478
The doctor told me something,

297
00:29:11,187 --> 00:29:13,690
but I can't understand a word he said.

298
00:29:14,274 --> 00:29:16,317
Maybe I'm going deaf.

299
00:29:16,401 --> 00:29:18,319
I can hear one moment
and can't hear the next.

300
00:29:19,362 --> 00:29:23,199
Gosh, I know you're busy with work.
I'm sorry about this.

301
00:29:23,283 --> 00:29:24,450
Well,

302
00:29:24,534 --> 00:29:27,787
I can make the afternoon visiting hours.
I have today and tomorrow off.

303
00:29:28,955 --> 00:29:31,249
Grandpa, I'll be right there.

304
00:29:49,893 --> 00:29:52,312
Her intracranial pressure
and blood pressure are unstable.

305
00:29:52,395 --> 00:29:54,230
She hasn't regained consciousness,

306
00:29:54,314 --> 00:29:56,733
so we can't move her
to a regular room as planned.

307
00:29:56,816 --> 00:29:59,903
Why did the numbers
suddenly change like that?

308
00:30:00,486 --> 00:30:03,031
They're still changing,
so we'll have to keep monitoring her.

309
00:30:03,114 --> 00:30:06,409
Can her condition worsen
as she regains consciousness?

310
00:30:06,492 --> 00:30:08,077
What are her chances of getting better?

311
00:30:09,579 --> 00:30:11,497
It's hard to say at this point.

312
00:30:11,581 --> 00:30:13,499
No, the numbers.

313
00:30:13,583 --> 00:30:16,002
-You can just tell me in terms of numbers.
-Tae-seo.

314
00:30:31,267 --> 00:30:33,144
Grandma, I'm here.

315
00:30:33,227 --> 00:30:34,646
You can hear me, right?

316
00:30:34,729 --> 00:30:36,147
I thought you'd be bored,

317
00:30:36,230 --> 00:30:38,191
so I'm here in place of the TV.

318
00:30:38,274 --> 00:30:42,445
I'm going to be here
instead of Tae-seo starting tomorrow.

319
00:30:42,528 --> 00:30:43,821
Hyang-gi is coming too.

320
00:30:44,405 --> 00:30:47,241
I know you're really close with her.
Isn't that great?

321
00:31:31,119 --> 00:31:32,453
Okay. Get out gently.

322
00:31:32,537 --> 00:31:33,871
Hey, lean on here.

323
00:31:33,955 --> 00:31:35,164
Careful.

324
00:31:35,248 --> 00:31:36,916
Wait, hold on.

325
00:31:37,583 --> 00:31:38,668
Tae-seo.

326
00:31:39,210 --> 00:31:40,211
Tae-seo!

327
00:31:40,878 --> 00:31:42,422
Over here.

328
00:31:42,505 --> 00:31:43,840
-I'll do it.
-Okay.

329
00:31:45,049 --> 00:31:46,467
-Lower one leg first.
-Okay.

330
00:31:49,345 --> 00:31:50,388
Slowly.

331
00:31:58,813 --> 00:32:00,440
Goodness.

332
00:32:00,523 --> 00:32:01,524
Here.

333
00:32:02,066 --> 00:32:03,443
Pour that out and add fresh water.

334
00:32:16,122 --> 00:32:17,331
After your parents passed away

335
00:32:17,415 --> 00:32:19,292
and when your grandma was bedridden,

336
00:32:20,376 --> 00:32:22,587
I cooked rice
for the first time in my life.

337
00:32:23,546 --> 00:32:24,964
You should learn how to do it.

338
00:32:25,548 --> 00:32:29,427
Your grandma was worried
about you always eating out.

339
00:32:34,057 --> 00:32:35,141
Later on,

340
00:32:35,892 --> 00:32:37,769
when the person beside you gets sick,

341
00:32:39,020 --> 00:32:41,522
you should at least
cook them proper meals.

342
00:32:44,108 --> 00:32:44,984
Okay.

343
00:33:05,129 --> 00:33:05,963
Hui-seo.

344
00:33:26,734 --> 00:33:27,652
Hui-seo!

345
00:33:27,735 --> 00:33:29,403
The healthy ones should do what they can.

346
00:33:29,487 --> 00:33:31,155
Get out of there. It's too dangerous.

347
00:33:31,239 --> 00:33:32,573
-Yeon Hui-seo.
-There they are.

348
00:33:32,657 --> 00:33:33,574
Get out right now!

349
00:33:34,492 --> 00:33:35,910
Let go!

350
00:33:35,993 --> 00:33:38,204
Don't follow me. Go find some yourself.

351
00:33:52,927 --> 00:33:53,845
Tae-seo.

352
00:33:55,221 --> 00:33:56,764
I've never seen anything like this.

353
00:33:59,892 --> 00:34:01,727
How can it be this dark?

354
00:34:03,479 --> 00:34:05,106
The whole world is pitch black.

355
00:34:06,649 --> 00:34:08,025
It's just endless darkness.

356
00:34:14,615 --> 00:34:17,076
Is this what despair looks like?

357
00:34:29,755 --> 00:34:32,967
What happened before won't happen again.

358
00:34:35,678 --> 00:34:40,641
You were there alone
outside Mom's ICU room.

359
00:34:42,185 --> 00:34:43,769
Grandma told me.

360
00:34:44,687 --> 00:34:48,274
She said she felt sorry
towards you the most.

361
00:34:51,777 --> 00:34:53,905
After she collapsed,

362
00:34:55,114 --> 00:34:56,532
Grandpa couldn't go right away.

363
00:34:58,659 --> 00:35:00,119
And you were left all by yourself.

364
00:35:02,121 --> 00:35:03,706
Seven hours for Dad.

365
00:35:04,498 --> 00:35:05,791
Two days for Mom.

366
00:35:07,543 --> 00:35:09,962
She said you stayed outside the ICU
all by yourself.

367
00:35:14,550 --> 00:35:15,968
You must've felt so…

368
00:35:17,303 --> 00:35:18,846
helpless

369
00:35:19,931 --> 00:35:21,265
and scared.

370
00:35:27,730 --> 00:35:29,774
You were younger than I am now.

371
00:35:40,284 --> 00:35:41,244
Tae-seo.

372
00:35:43,913 --> 00:35:47,583
Grandma will be right back on her feet
for your sake, if nothing else.

373
00:37:08,122 --> 00:37:09,540
This is nice.

374
00:37:09,623 --> 00:37:11,917
Watching the fire reminds me of that time.

375
00:37:12,001 --> 00:37:14,628
Eun-a, was it last year
or the year before that?

376
00:37:14,712 --> 00:37:15,838
That day the power went out.

377
00:37:16,756 --> 00:37:18,215
-It was last year.
-Last year?

378
00:37:18,299 --> 00:37:20,885
-The day we lit candles?
-Yeah, when we lit candles.

379
00:37:20,968 --> 00:37:22,928
Eun-a looked like she was about to cry.

380
00:37:23,012 --> 00:37:26,140
But Ga-on was so excited,
saying it felt like we were camping.

381
00:37:26,223 --> 00:37:28,642
-He was running around.
-Hello.

382
00:37:29,977 --> 00:37:31,645
-Ga-on.
-Uncle Seong-chan!

383
00:37:31,729 --> 00:37:32,646
Hey, Ga-on.

384
00:37:32,730 --> 00:37:34,190
-What's going on?
-Seong-chan.

385
00:37:35,066 --> 00:37:37,485
Hey, I thought you couldn't make it.

386
00:37:38,069 --> 00:37:39,862
I should at least see you before you go.

387
00:37:40,613 --> 00:37:41,614
What's all this?

388
00:37:42,281 --> 00:37:44,075
-You bought something for us?
-Want a beer?

389
00:37:44,158 --> 00:37:46,285
-Thank you.
-Come sit down.

390
00:37:47,703 --> 00:37:49,705
-Thanks for coming when you're busy.
-It's nothing.

391
00:37:57,338 --> 00:37:58,464
What were you talking about?

392
00:37:58,547 --> 00:38:01,634
That time last year when the power
went out and Eun-a had a hard time.

393
00:38:01,717 --> 00:38:03,803
I still get chills
when I think about that day.

394
00:38:13,396 --> 00:38:15,064
I'll just sober up a bit.

395
00:38:16,107 --> 00:38:17,525
I drove my car here.

396
00:38:24,824 --> 00:38:26,033
Dong-sik came by, right?

397
00:38:27,368 --> 00:38:29,328
It's hard to book him
for house calls, you know.

398
00:38:30,579 --> 00:38:32,790
Man, that guy is good at his job.

399
00:38:33,833 --> 00:38:35,751
We have to return this
to its original state,

400
00:38:36,335 --> 00:38:37,962
so it's better to just repair it now.

401
00:38:39,088 --> 00:38:41,340
This is all I'll say
as your business partner.

402
00:38:42,341 --> 00:38:44,051
I know you'll manage the rest on your own.

403
00:38:48,722 --> 00:38:50,307
Why are you drinking?

404
00:38:52,309 --> 00:38:53,894
I can't even drive anyway.

405
00:38:59,442 --> 00:39:02,778
Even if it's late,
call Dong-sik if anything happens.

406
00:39:03,487 --> 00:39:05,698
He's the most reliable one around here.

407
00:39:07,908 --> 00:39:09,368
Since I'll be moving somewhere else,

408
00:39:12,371 --> 00:39:13,622
I came to say goodbye.

409
00:39:15,291 --> 00:39:16,750
Where are you going?

410
00:39:17,793 --> 00:39:19,044
Jeju Island.

411
00:39:21,422 --> 00:39:23,174
I got the offer a while ago,

412
00:39:24,550 --> 00:39:26,093
but I think I can go now.

413
00:39:32,892 --> 00:39:33,976
Still…

414
00:39:35,352 --> 00:39:36,937
if you're ever in trouble,

415
00:39:38,272 --> 00:39:39,857
you can call me.

416
00:39:39,940 --> 00:39:41,734
As your former colleague,

417
00:39:41,817 --> 00:39:43,444
I can take care of that much.

418
00:39:45,738 --> 00:39:48,324
What I can't stand the most
about Park So-hyeon is

419
00:39:48,407 --> 00:39:51,160
she never lets go of any relationships.

420
00:39:51,243 --> 00:39:53,662
She's friends with all her exes.

421
00:39:55,080 --> 00:39:56,999
She'll come up with any excuse.

422
00:39:58,250 --> 00:39:59,418
It's a talent.

423
00:40:00,085 --> 00:40:02,505
She makes friends
without offending anyone.

424
00:40:04,798 --> 00:40:05,633
Here.

425
00:40:06,342 --> 00:40:07,760
It's the one you've been saving.

426
00:40:19,188 --> 00:40:21,565
I brought this on the day
we opened the guesthouse.

427
00:40:21,649 --> 00:40:25,277
I was going to open it that day,
but it was so hectic.

428
00:40:27,947 --> 00:40:28,864
Keep it here.

429
00:40:31,700 --> 00:40:34,912
You said it's really expensive. Take it.

430
00:40:39,291 --> 00:40:41,043
Your dad gave that to me.

431
00:40:42,044 --> 00:40:43,879
He got rid of all his alcohol.

432
00:40:44,463 --> 00:40:46,382
He was serious about quitting.

433
00:40:47,550 --> 00:40:50,177
He gave it to me,
saying it was his most prized bottle.

434
00:40:51,220 --> 00:40:56,433
I was planning on drinking it with you
when we had something to celebrate.

435
00:40:57,434 --> 00:40:58,269
You can have it.

436
00:41:04,233 --> 00:41:06,485
Don't drink it
when you're feeling down, okay?

437
00:41:06,986 --> 00:41:08,320
It's only for celebrating.

438
00:41:10,322 --> 00:41:13,242
I'd never seen my dad
give anyone a gift before.

439
00:41:16,996 --> 00:41:18,914
He wasn't very good
at connecting with people.

440
00:41:20,207 --> 00:41:22,418
He must've really wanted you to have it.

441
00:41:26,547 --> 00:41:27,423
It's yours.

442
00:41:36,432 --> 00:41:37,391
Let's drink it today.

443
00:41:39,018 --> 00:41:40,644
It's a day worth celebrating.

444
00:41:45,691 --> 00:41:48,319
The relationship you're sick and tired of
is finally over,

445
00:41:48,402 --> 00:41:49,278
so you can celebrate.

446
00:41:52,990 --> 00:41:54,867
You're not good with wine,

447
00:41:54,950 --> 00:41:56,452
so I can drink it by myself.

448
00:42:05,419 --> 00:42:06,670
Just have a taste.

449
00:42:37,701 --> 00:42:39,161
You acted like you wouldn't return.

450
00:42:39,244 --> 00:42:40,954
You said you'd clean it out.

451
00:42:41,955 --> 00:42:43,916
It reminded me of that truck.

452
00:42:45,084 --> 00:42:46,794
Those damn scumbags.

453
00:42:49,880 --> 00:42:51,465
You don't regret coming back, right?

454
00:42:54,426 --> 00:42:55,844
I need to do well from now on

455
00:42:56,720 --> 00:42:58,555
so I don't end up regretting it.

456
00:43:02,101 --> 00:43:04,436
I'm glad I faced those scumbags.

457
00:43:06,188 --> 00:43:07,648
You have that effect.

458
00:43:08,649 --> 00:43:09,483
When I look at you,

459
00:43:10,192 --> 00:43:11,235
it all feels worthwhile.

460
00:43:15,155 --> 00:43:18,534
You said you depended on me a lot,

461
00:43:20,119 --> 00:43:21,870
but I might have depended on you more.

462
00:43:22,788 --> 00:43:25,708
You were always good to me.

463
00:43:36,719 --> 00:43:39,596
The times we spent as colleagues together

464
00:43:40,347 --> 00:43:41,348
were good times.

465
00:43:51,316 --> 00:43:53,318
We'd finish the day's work,

466
00:43:53,402 --> 00:43:56,780
wind down while having a beer here,

467
00:43:57,906 --> 00:43:59,450
and make new plans.

468
00:44:00,033 --> 00:44:01,118
It was our routine,

469
00:44:02,453 --> 00:44:04,413
but I guess this is the last time.

470
00:44:11,587 --> 00:44:12,671
What are you doing?

471
00:44:14,214 --> 00:44:15,132
No, I just…

472
00:44:15,215 --> 00:44:16,675
What, you think I'll try something?

473
00:44:16,759 --> 00:44:18,427
No, that's not it.

474
00:44:31,565 --> 00:44:34,026
I'll leave quietly at dawn
once I've sobered up,

475
00:44:34,943 --> 00:44:36,445
so let's just say goodbye now.

476
00:44:40,908 --> 00:44:42,034
Take care.

477
00:44:49,500 --> 00:44:50,584
Also,

478
00:44:51,335 --> 00:44:52,920
that truck won't be coming here again.

479
00:44:53,003 --> 00:44:55,881
But if it does, don't confront them
and just call the police.

480
00:44:55,964 --> 00:44:57,299
Or at least call Dong-sik.

481
00:44:58,509 --> 00:44:59,510
You'll end up in trouble.

482
00:45:00,302 --> 00:45:02,638
Okay, I got it. I'll stay away from them.

483
00:45:07,059 --> 00:45:08,310
Now, I feel relieved.

484
00:46:24,428 --> 00:46:26,763
She said it wasn't that house.

485
00:47:41,129 --> 00:47:44,591
HUI-SEO

486
00:48:17,958 --> 00:48:19,459
MISSED CALL
HUI-SEO

487
00:48:48,029 --> 00:48:49,406
What brings you here at this hour?

488
00:48:50,407 --> 00:48:51,241
Tell me.

489
00:48:53,577 --> 00:48:55,162
Who are you?

490
00:49:07,841 --> 00:49:08,884
Hey.

491
00:49:11,720 --> 00:49:13,138
Hey, get out.

492
00:49:18,059 --> 00:49:19,811
I said get out!

493
00:50:07,108 --> 00:50:10,237
HUI-SEO

494
00:51:12,007 --> 00:51:13,925
What is he doing here?

495
00:51:15,427 --> 00:51:16,261
Eun-a.

496
00:51:17,637 --> 00:51:18,930
Is that why Seoul…

497
00:51:26,271 --> 00:51:28,607
You're worse than Park So-hyeon.

498
00:52:33,546 --> 00:52:34,547
Tae-seo.

499
00:52:36,049 --> 00:52:40,011
This is how the world looks again.

500
00:53:18,842 --> 00:53:20,677
SEOUL (GANGNAM) EXPRESS

501
00:53:22,012 --> 00:53:24,848
TICKET OFFICE

502
00:53:24,931 --> 00:53:27,809
YEON NAMSAN

503
00:53:41,656 --> 00:53:43,616
Grandma isn't waking up.

504
00:53:45,869 --> 00:53:47,495
I'm afraid, and I'm exhausted.

505
00:53:48,246 --> 00:53:49,664
Let's meet.

506
00:54:00,008 --> 00:54:03,178
DAEJEON SERVICE AREA

507
00:54:38,379 --> 00:54:40,340
They said Grandma
isn't responding to any stimuli.

508
00:54:41,716 --> 00:54:43,676
The pressure in her head keeps rising.

509
00:54:44,761 --> 00:54:45,970
And she's now in a coma.

510
00:54:47,555 --> 00:54:48,515
Where are you, Tae-seo?

511
00:56:26,905 --> 00:56:28,740
Did you…

512
00:56:29,574 --> 00:56:30,617
see the doctor?

513
00:56:31,868 --> 00:56:33,244
What did he say?

514
00:56:39,876 --> 00:56:40,919
What do we do?

515
00:56:41,628 --> 00:56:43,046
It's not yet…

516
00:57:33,012 --> 00:57:34,305
Mom…

517
00:57:35,056 --> 00:57:36,307
Mom.

518
00:58:33,781 --> 00:58:35,783
CALLS
YEON NAMSAN

519
00:59:06,648 --> 00:59:09,108
The back house is basically
the management office.

520
00:59:10,109 --> 00:59:13,905
We come and go,
and we each have a separate room…

521
00:59:23,247 --> 00:59:26,542
GRANDMA ISN'T WAKING UP
I'M AFRAID, AND I'M EXHAUSTED

522
00:59:26,626 --> 00:59:28,044
LET'S MEET

523
01:01:08,519 --> 01:01:12,940
MISSED CALL
EUN-A

524
01:01:32,710 --> 01:01:33,878
Tae-seo.

525
01:01:37,840 --> 01:01:39,050
Earlier…

526
01:01:43,137 --> 01:01:44,430
Earlier…

527
01:01:45,598 --> 01:01:46,682
Eun-a.

528
01:01:47,266 --> 01:01:48,893
Let me explain.

529
01:01:49,769 --> 01:01:51,896
-Earlier…
-You don't need to explain.

530
01:01:56,901 --> 01:01:58,361
Right now…

531
01:02:08,412 --> 01:02:10,206
it's all too much for me.

532
01:02:18,130 --> 01:02:19,298
You're right,

533
01:02:21,759 --> 01:02:23,052
and I'm right too.

534
01:02:25,096 --> 01:02:26,305
That place is right for you,

535
01:02:31,352 --> 01:02:32,937
and this place is right for me.

536
01:02:41,279 --> 01:02:42,530
We should both…

537
01:02:53,416 --> 01:02:55,668
forget the past month.

538
01:03:03,718 --> 01:03:04,719
All right.

539
01:03:08,472 --> 01:03:09,724
Let's do that.

540
01:03:12,310 --> 01:03:13,644
I understand.

541
01:03:14,937 --> 01:03:16,439
That's what we'll do.

542
01:03:27,074 --> 01:03:28,075
I'm sorry.

543
01:03:51,432 --> 01:03:54,936
STILL SHINING

544
01:04:20,795 --> 01:04:23,089
Goodbyes are terrifying to me.

545
01:04:23,673 --> 01:04:25,800
Trying to make things work,

546
01:04:27,093 --> 01:04:28,886
intruding into your peaceful life…

547
01:04:29,971 --> 01:04:31,013
Enough.

548
01:04:31,931 --> 01:04:33,015
Let's go out for real.

549
01:04:34,058 --> 01:04:35,518
We missed each other.

550
01:04:37,728 --> 01:04:38,854
A few days ago…

551
01:04:39,480 --> 01:04:40,731
She came to your house.

552
01:04:42,233 --> 01:04:43,442
Is it okay

553
01:04:44,276 --> 01:04:45,987
to go back to you like this?

554
01:04:47,863 --> 01:04:48,864
Mo Eun-a.

555
01:04:53,494 --> 01:04:55,496
Subtitle translation by: Hyesoo Lee
